gate: OPEN
v:4 role:dev x:nextjs-tailwind
task: S03 T1 — #527 Footer WCAG 2.5.5 tap target: re-measure on prod, then conditional fix
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND]
sprint: S03
repos: [crop-front]
branch: issue-527

context: |
  Issue #527 was filed against a 4-column footer that was redesigned in sprint 4
  (2026-05-15, commit f7c550db) — the "Shop by Models" column was dropped entirely.
  The measurement table in the original issue references links that no longer exist.
  The audit update (2026-06-01) says: FooterLink default variant still has no vertical
  padding (text-sm, no py, no min-h), so the <24px problem likely persists on the
  remaining columns (Shop by Brand, Help & Support, legal row, address/phone links).
  BUT this MUST be re-measured before any code change.
  Root cause if still present: layout/Footer/Footer.tsx:104 — FooterLink default
  renders bare <Link> with text-sm (17px) and no vertical padding.

steps:
  STEP 1 — Re-measure on prod (required; do before branching or writing any code):
    1. Open https://crop.clintontractor.net/ in DevTools mobile emulation:
       viewport 390×844, DPR=3, touch=true.
    2. Scroll to footer.
    3. Run the verification snippet (from issue body):
       [...document.querySelectorAll('footer a, footer button, footer [role="button"]')]
         .filter(e => { const r = e.getBoundingClientRect(); return r.width > 0 && r.height > 0 && Math.min(r.width, r.height) < 24; })
         .map(e => ({ label: e.textContent?.trim(), w: Math.round(e.getBoundingClientRect().width), h: Math.round(e.getBoundingClientRect().height) }));
    4. Post the output (screenshot or table) as a comment on issue #527.
    5. Branch: git checkout -b issue-527 dev (only AFTER posting the comment)

  STEP 2A — If snippet returns [] (no violations):
    - Footer is already compliant post-redesign.
    - Comment on #527: "Re-measured on prod 2026-06-01, viewport 390x844 — snippet returns [].
      Zero footer links <24px. Closing as fixed-by-redesign (sprint 4, commit f7c550db)."
    - Close the issue. No code change needed. Task complete.

  STEP 2B — If snippet returns violations:
    1. Fix: layout/Footer/Footer.tsx → FooterLink default return (lines ~104-113):
       Add py-1.5 to the className. This gives 17px text + 12px padding = 29px tap height.
       Do NOT change the "all" variant or the ul gap-2 — those don't need touching.
    2. Also sweep the sibling surfaces per issue:
       - Footer legal links (text-xs row at bottom) — same pattern, same fix if failing
       - Footer address link (flex items-start gap-2.5) — should be ok but verify
       - Footer social icons (size-12 = 48px) — confirm still passing
    3. Create/update layout/Footer/Footer.test.tsx:
       Regression guard — render <Footer />, query all links inside footer, assert each
       has 'py-' in its className (jsdom can't compute layout, so className assertion is
       the guard). Pattern: import Footer, render, getAllByRole('link') within footer,
       check classList contains py-1.5.
    4. Add Playwright test tests/e2e/footer-tap-targets.spec.ts:
       On 390×844 viewport, every footer a/button getBoundingClientRect() minDim ≥ 24px.
       (Issue body specifies this as the regression guard — it's mandatory.)
    5. Commit: fix(footer): add py-1.5 to FooterLink for WCAG 2.5.5 tap target (#527)
       No Co-Authored-By, no emoji.
    6. Open draft PR into dev, reference #527, include Step 1 measurement + Step 2 after screenshot.

cmd:
  - bun run lint:fix
  - bun run type-check
  - bunx vitest run layout/Footer/Footer.test.tsx
  - bunx playwright test tests/e2e/footer-tap-targets.spec.ts --project=chromium (if test written)

out:
  - issue #527 comment with prod measurement (Step 1)
  - layout/Footer/Footer.tsx (patched, only if violations confirmed)
  - layout/Footer/Footer.test.tsx (regression guard, only if fix applied)
  - tests/e2e/footer-tap-targets.spec.ts (Playwright test, only if fix applied)

done:
  - Step 1 measurement comment posted on #527
  - EITHER: issue closed as fixed-by-redesign with evidence
  - OR: snippet returns [] on prod after PR merge; Playwright test green; PR reviewed by appdev-v
